article.headline: Sacramento State 77, Montana State 71
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Cedric Thompkins scored a career-high 22 points on 10-of-11 shooting, and Sacramento State snapped a three-game losing streak with a 77-71 victory over Montana State on Thursday night. Brandon Guyton added 16 points and Joseth Dawson had 11 for the Hornets (8-11, 2-4 Big Sky Conference), who won for just the second time in seven games by holding off the Bobcats (11-8, 3-3) in a frenetic second half. Both teams scored 49 points apiece after Sacramento State took a 28-22 halftime lead. Montana State held a nine-point lead midway through the second half after making an 11-0 run, but the Hornets scored on 13 of their last 15 possessions. Jason Erickson scored 24 points for Montana State, which entered the game in second place in the Big Sky. Josh Barsh added 12 points for the Bobcats, who had won eight of their last 10. Montana State has lost five straight in Sacramento.
